         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper we apply number-theoretic results to estimate the dispersion, a measure of denseness for sequences in a bounded set, of the Halton and Hammersley sequences in the hypercube $I^s = \lbrack0, 1\rbrack^s$. It is seen that they attain the minimal order of magnitude for the dispersion.</p>
          </abstract>
